    StrategyA
    Creates a StrategyA object in a singleton design pattern Performs trade using the appropriate rules Rule: "If the price of BTC < 50,000 and the price of ADA > 2, then buy 10 ADA"
    StrategyB
    Creates a StrategyB object in a singleton design pattern Performs trade using the appropriate rules Rule: "If the price of ADA < $2, and the price of ETH < $3500, then buy ADA of worth $1000"
    StrategyC
    Creates a StrategyC object in a singleton design pattern Performs trade using the appropriate rules Rule: "If the price of ADA > $3, and the price of BTC < $50, then buy 50 BTC"
    StrategyFactory
    This strategy factory returns the appropriate strategy type depending on the parameter provided by the client
    StrategyInterface
    StrategyInterface is used by StrategyA, StrategyB, and StrategyC The methods are overridden by each Strategy class
